# Podium
**Category:** ventures
**Domain:** customer communication / SaaS
**Website:** [podium.com](https://www.podium.com)

## Overview
Podium provides a cloud-based customer communication platform designed for local businesses. Its core product enables businesses to manage text messaging, online reviews, payments, and web chat from a single inbox, helping them engage with customers and streamline operations. The platform integrates with popular business tools and offers features such as automated review requests, two-way SMS, and payment links.

Founded in 2014, Podium quickly grew into one of Utah’s most prominent technology unicorns, reaching a valuation of over $1 billion by 2019. The company serves tens of thousands of businesses across North America, particularly in service industries like automotive, healthcare, home services, and retail. Podium’s mission is to help local businesses thrive in the digital age by making customer interactions seamless and efficient.

## Utah connection
Podium is headquartered in Lehi, Utah, and was born out of the state’s growing Silicon Slopes tech ecosystem. The company’s success has helped cement Utah’s reputation as a hub for SaaS startups and unicorn exits. It has raised significant venture capital from investors such as Accel, Summit Partners, and GV (Google Ventures), and its leadership frequently participates in local tech events and mentorship programs. Podium’s growth has also contributed to job creation in the region, employing thousands of people in the Lehi area.

